CP14HerbalBandage.description: A bandage net woven from grass, not the most reliable or useful thing, but better than nothing.

CP14Gauze.name: gauze
CP14Gauze.description: Dense cloth gauze, to prevent valuable blood from leaking out of the body.

CP14EnergyCrystalBase.description: A crystal shard capable of storing magical energy.

CP14BaseEssence.name: magic essence
CP14BaseEssence.description: Particles of magical energy polarised into a particular type of magic. Will be gone soon, so try to collect them as soon as possible!

CP14RitualChalk.name: ritual chalk
CP14RitualChalk.description: Quartz chalk, handy for drawing temporary ritual circles.

CP14BaseDemiplaneKey.name: demiplane coordinate key
CP14BaseDemiplaneKey.description: A temporary blob of energy linking the real world and the demiplane. Use it before it dissipates.

CP14Rope.name: rope
CP14Rope.description: Multifunctional rope. You can tie something with it. Or someone.

CP14Scissors.name: scissors
CP14Scissors.description: A tool for shredding wool, hair, clothing, and, if not handled carefully, even fingers.

CP14Screwdriver.name: screwdriver
CP14Screwdriver.description: Industrial grade torque in a small screwdriving package.

CP14BaseSharpeningStone.name: sharpening stone
CP14BaseSharpeningStone.description: Allows you to sharpen blunted weapons. If you overdo it, you may well sharpen the weapon completely.

CP14BaseWallpaper.description: Thin paper wallpaper. You can glue them on the walls from different sides, or peel them off with any sharp object.

CP14MagicShadowStaff.name: magic shadow staff
CP14MagicShadowStaff.description: A long, half-tech, half-magic stick designed to convert magical energy into shadow spells.

CP14ModularIronArrow.name: iron arrow
CP14ModularIronArrow.description: Standard arrow, balance between damage and reliability.

CP14ModularMithrilArrow.name: mithril arrow
CP14ModularMithrilArrow.description: An arrow made of expensive wood and magical iron, you shoot money, but the damage matches.

CP14ModularCopperArrow.name: copper arrow
CP14ModularCopperArrow.description: It's the cheapest and weakest arrow you've ever seen, but it's better than nothing.

CP14ModularIronAxe.name: iron axe
CP14ModularIronAxe.description: A heavy axe for cutting firewood or heads.

CP14ModularIronDagger.name: iron dagger
CP14ModularIronDagger.description: A small, multi-purpose, sharp blade. You can cut meat or throw it at a goblin.

CP14ModularIronDaggerTundra.name: Dagger Tundra
CP14ModularIronDaggerTundra.description: A small, multi-purpose, sharp blade. You can cut meat or throw it at a goblin. It has "tundra" engraved on it.

CP14ModularIronDaggerAgony.name: Dagger Agony
CP14ModularIronDaggerAgony.description: A small, multi-purpose, sharp blade. You can cut meat or throw it at a goblin. It has "agony" engraved on it.

CP14ModularIronHammer.name: iron hammer
CP14ModularIronHammer.description: A small hammer. Good for carpentry work as well as for cracking skulls.

CP14ModularIronHoe.name: iron hoe
CP14ModularIronHoe.description: Hoe. Your perfect tool for tilling the ground and preparing it for gardening.

CP14ModularIronMace.name: iron mace
CP14ModularIronMace.description: A heavy piece of metal on a long stick. What could be simpler than that?

CP14ModularIronPickaxe.name: iron pickaxe
CP14ModularIronPickaxe.description: Notched to perfection, for jamming it into rocks

CP14ModularGuildmasterRapier.name: guildmaster's personal rapier
CP14ModularGuildmasterRapier.description: A personal weapon issued to each guildmaster. Combines reliability and killing power.

CP14ModularIronShovel.name: iron shovel
CP14ModularIronShovel.description: An implement for digging up earth, digging beds or graves.

CP14ModularIronSickle.name: iron sickle
CP14ModularIronSickle.description: Originally developed as a weapon against grass, the sickle suddenly proved itself good at the bloodier harvest as well.

CP14ModularIronSpear.name: iron spear
CP14ModularIronSpear.description: The spear is a weapon whose effectiveness has stood the test of time.

CP14ModularIronKunai.name: iron kunai
CP14ModularIronKunai.description: An effective throwing weapon. Throw it at a wall, or no, better yet, at a goblin!

CP14ModularIronSword.name: iron sword
CP14ModularIronSword.description: the gold standard of edged weapons. Medium length, comfortable grip. No frills.

CP14ModularGuardHalberd.name: guard's halberd
CP14ModularGuardHalberd.description: The standard issue armament of the imperial guard. A long iron halberd adorned with blue feathers and brass

CP14BowCombat.name: combat bow
CP14BowCombat.description: A standard ranged weapon, and even without magic.

CP14BowIceArtifact.name: ice bow
CP14BowIceArtifact.description: A magic bow that needs no ammunition.

CP14BaseLightCrossbow.name: light crossbow
CP14BaseLightCrossbow.description: A small, compact crossbow that is comfortable to hold with one hand. Not too accurate on the reverse side.

CP14CrossboltIron.name: iron crossbow bolt
CP14CrossboltIron.description: Rod with a pointed spike in iron. No plumage, they're not bows.

CP14CrossboltGold.name: gold crossbow bolt
CP14CrossboltGold.description: Rod with a pointed spike in gold. No plumage, they're not bows.

CP14CrossboltCopper.name: copper crossbow bolt
CP14CrossboltCopper.description: Rod with a pointed spike in copper. No plumage, they're not bows.

CP14CrossboltMithril.name: mithril crossbow bolt
CP14CrossboltMithril.description: Rod with a pointed spike in mithril. No plumage, they're not bows.

CP14SpikeWhistle.name: spike
CP14SpikeWhistle.description: Organically spiked with an unknown liquid inside.

CP14DPSMeter.name: DPS Meter
CP14DPSMeter.description: Counts the average damage per second. If you stop hitting it, it shows the result.

CP14RoundLeaver.name: distance fog
CP14RoundLeaver.description: You have reached the edge of the game map. There's nothing further. You can use this fog to get out of the game.

CP14StoneWell.name: well
CP14StoneWell.description: At the bottom of this well gurgles clear water. If you have a bucket, you can reach it.

CP14LaddersDownBase.name: stairway down
CP14LaddersDownBase.description: The dark depths of the underworld are calling you.

CP14LaddersUpBase.name: stairway up
CP14LaddersUpBase.description: A way out of the dark underworld into the overworld.

CP14WallmountFlagAlchemist.name: alchemist tapestry
CP14WallmountFlagAlchemist.description: A tapestry with a potion symbol, indicating that alchemists dwell here.

CP14WallmountFlagBlacksmith.name: blacksmith tapestry
CP14WallmountFlagBlacksmith.description: A tapestry with a anvil symbol, indicating that blacksmiths dwell here.

CP14WallmountFlagTavern.name: tavern tapestry
CP14WallmountFlagTavern.description: A tapestry with a beer symbol, indicating that tavern is here.

CP14WallmountFlagBank.name: bank tapestry
CP14WallmountFlagBank.description: A tapestry with a coins symbol indicating that this is where the bankers live.

CP14WallmountFlagBankVault.name: bank vault tapestry
CP14WallmountFlagBankVault.description: A tapestry with a vault symbol indicating that this is where the bank vaults reside.

CP14WallmountFlagBankCrates.name: bank crates tapestry
CP14WallmountFlagBankCrates.description: A tapestry with a crates symbol indicating that this is where the bank vaults reside.

CP14WallmountFlagBankShip.name: bank ship tapestry
CP14WallmountFlagBankShip.description: A tapestry with a ship symbol denoting that there is a ship here to trade with the city.

CP14WallmountFlagBankCommandant.name: commandant tapestry
CP14WallmountFlagBankCommandant.description: A tapestry with a star symbol indicating that the commandant lives here.

CP14WallmountFlagGuardSwords.name: guard tapestry
CP14WallmountFlagGuardSwords.description: A tapestry with a swords symbol denoting that the guards are here.

CP14WallmountFlagGuardShield.name: guard tapestry
CP14WallmountFlagGuardShield.description: A tapestry with a shield symbol denoting that the guards are here.

CP14WallmountFlagGuardCommander.name: guard commander tapestry
CP14WallmountFlagGuardCommander.description: A tapestry with a star symbol indicating that the Guard Commandant lives here.

CP14WallmountPaintingCandle.name: candle painting
CP14WallmountPaintingCandle.description: A nicely drawn candle in a frame.

CP14WallmountPaintingWoman.name: painting of a woman
CP14WallmountPaintingWoman.description: The painting depicts a woman with a mysterious smile.

CP14WallmountPaintingSaint.name: painting of a saint
CP14WallmountPaintingSaint.description: A drawing of a nun with a halo over her head. This is how you can feel the holiness of the picture.

CP14StatueAngel.name: angel statue
CP14StatueAngel.description: A divine statue of a praying angel.

CP14StatueStoneHeadHigh.name: stone head
CP14StatueStoneHeadHigh.description: Strange stone heads, they seem to be watching.

CP14StatueWizard.name: statue wizard
CP14StatueWizard.description: A statue of a magician holding magic.

CP14BaseTombstone.name: tombstone
CP14BaseTombstone.description: A piece of stone placed in memory of the dead.

CP14BaseFenceBig.name: big fence
CP14BaseFenceBig.description: You definitely need a towel to get to the other side

CP14BaseFenceGateBig.name: fence big gate
CP14BaseFenceGateBig.description: Big man-sized gates. What's your next move?

CP14Cliff.name: cliff
CP14Cliff.description: Severe unevenness of the natural landscape.

CP14BaseFence.name: fence
CP14BaseFence.description: A low fence restricting movement in a purely nominal way.

CP14BaseFenceGate.name: fence gate
CP14BaseFenceGate.description: You have two paths. You can open the door like a normal person, or you can climb over the door like a funny person.

CP14BaseFenceWindow.name: fence window
CP14BaseFenceWindow.description: You can slip an object in here, but you sure as hell can't fit through.

CP14Chasm.name: chasm
CP14Chasm.description: You can't even see the bottom.

CP14FloorLava.name: lava
CP14FloorLava.description: Don't jump in. It's not worth it, no matter how funny it is.

CP14FloorWaterOptimized.name: water
CP14FloorWaterOptimized.description: A trough of plain water. Clean enough for consumption

CP14DemiplaneHint.name: astral crack
CP14DemiplaneHint.description: Those cracks always lead to a way out of the damn place

CP14HighBush.name: high bush
CP14HighBush.description: Very tall and dense thickets. Perhaps someone is watching you from them

CP14BaseRock.name: rock
CP14BaseRock.description: A piece of rock. Hard, heavy, useless.

CP14RoyalPumpkin.name: royal pumpkin
CP14RoyalPumpkin.description: It's a huge pumpkin, it feels like you could even make a carriage out of it.

CP14Snowdrift.name: snowdrift
CP14Snowdrift.description: A big, cold pile of snow.

CP14BaseTree.name: tree
CP14BaseTree.description: Decades of life and growth, saturating the surrounding nature with fresh air.

CP14CrystalBase.name: quartz
CP14CrystalBase.description: Natural quartz crystals that can absorb the magical energy of the world around them.

CP14PlantCabbage.name: cabbage
CP14PlantCabbage.description: You see a cabbage in front of you. Perhaps you were born in one.

CP14PlantCotton.name: cotton
CP14PlantCotton.description: In a way, you're growing future clothes.

CP14PlantCucumber.name: cucumber
CP14PlantCucumber.description: Don't trust people who know how to turn into pickles.

CP14PlantOnion.name: onion
CP14PlantOnion.description: He's so cute it brings tears to my eyes to cut him up.

CP14PlantPepper.name: pepper
CP14PlantPepper.description: Russian roulette. Are you hot, or are you sweet peppers?

CP14PlantPotato.name: potato
CP14PlantPotato.description: Some like to associate themselves with potatoes. People like that are not bad people.

CP14PlantPumpkin.name: pumpkin
CP14PlantPumpkin.description: Legends say there is a pumpkin king who stares into your soul through the crowns of trees.

CP14PlantSage.name: sage
CP14PlantSage.description: Medicinal sage. Some love it for its medicinal properties, others for its narcotic properties. Which side are you on?

CP14PlantTomatoes.name: tomatoes
CP14PlantTomatoes.description: On the one hand, it's a delicious fruit. But why eat it when it's much more fun to use tomatoes as a throwing projectile?

CP14PlantWheat.name: wheat
CP14PlantWheat.description: Most popular crop. Unpretentious, it opens the way to an abundance of flour products.

CP14GatherableBloodFlower.name: blood rose
CP14GatherableBloodFlower.description: Scarlet flowers growing where blood has been spilled.

CP14GatherableBlueAmanita.name: blue Amanita
CP14GatherableBlueAmanita.description: A sky blue flower known for its medicinal and magical properties.

CP14GatherableChromiumSlime.name: chromium slime
CP14GatherableChromiumSlime.description: This rare thick substance can be found in a stream of water as if it has a mind of its own. When trying to change the slime itself - the slime changes the reagent it interacts with.

CP14GatherableDayflin.name: yellow dayflin
CP14GatherableDayflin.description: A yellow sun flower that smells like melted milk. Can be processed into a yellow dye.

CP14GatherableFlyAgaric.name: fly agaric
CP14GatherableFlyAgaric.description: This poisonous mushroom can often be found near bodies of water or other wet areas. It is not recommended for consumption.

CP14GatherableLumiMushroom.name: lumishroom
CP14GatherableLumiMushroom.description: A faintly luminous mushroom. Often used by alchemists as a means of concentrating solutions.

CP14WaterLilies.name: water lilies
CP14WaterLilies.description: Wow, these are plants that don't grow on land, but on water! Nature is amazing.

CP14WaterReeds.name: reed
CP14WaterReeds.description: Usually grows in swamps and on river banks.

CP14GatherableWildSage.name: wild sage
CP14GatherableWildSage.description: Root of this ubiquitous medicinal plant not bad at healing physical injuries, and inducing coughing.

CP14Bonfire.name: bonfire
CP14Bonfire.description: A pile of logs stacked together, ready to burst into flames at the slightest spark.

CP14IronCabinet.name: iron cabinet
CP14IronCabinet.description: an iron cabinet. Sturdy, lockable. You can store your valuables here without fear of some burglar taking it all for himself.

CP14ClosetGlassShowcase.name: glass showcase
CP14ClosetGlassShowcase.description: Something of value can be placed here without fear of it being discreetly stolen!

CP14Lamppost.name: lamppost
CP14Lamppost.description: A lantern hanging from a pole.

CP14LamppostBlue.name: lamppost
CP14LamppostBlue.description: A lantern hanging from a pole.

CP14PottedPlantBase.name: potted plant
CP14PottedPlantBase.description: A domesticated plant in a clay pot, more plants.

CP14TableWooden.name: wooden table
CP14TableWooden.description: A simple table made of boards.

CP14TableWoodenRound.name: round wooden table
CP14TableWoodenRound.description: A simple table made of boards.

CP14BaseTorch.description: A good, reliable light source. Too bad it doesn't last.

CP14WallmountBarShelfA.name: bar shelf
CP14WallmountBarShelfA.description: Wall shelves to store your wine collection

CP14BaseRoof.name: roof
CP14BaseRoof.description: A roof over your head to protect you from the heat of the sun or the weather.

CP14AlchemyFurnace.name: alchemy furnace
CP14AlchemyFurnace.description: A furnace fueled by wood, coal, or any other burning material. Handy for heating your alchemical potions.

CP14BaseSharpeningStoneStructure.name: stationary sharpening stone
CP14BaseSharpeningStoneStructure.description: A strong, durable sharpening stone capable of sharpening weapons without much damage to them.

CP14DemiplanRiftCore.name: demiplan rift core
CP14DemiplanRiftCore.description: A subtle connection between the real world and the demiplane where the adventurers went. Sooner or later they will return from there.

CP14DemiplaneTimedRadiusPassway.name: pulsating demiplane rift
CP14DemiplaneTimedRadiusPassway.description: This rift is gaining strength, and will trap all nearby creatures in a demiplane in a second!

CP14DemiplanePassway.name: demiplane rift
CP14DemiplanePassway.description: A gap in space that allows you to travel between world and demiplanes.

CP14DemiplaneLinkCrystal.name: demiplane link crystal
CP14DemiplaneLinkCrystal.description: Maintains communication with the demiplanes while charged. Causes mosnters from the demiplanes to attack the city. Once it is discharged, the game is over.

CP14PortalFrameCrystal.name: portal frame
CP14PortalFrameCrystal.description: A structure made of shadow crystals used to create a stable portal to another location.

CP14DemiplaneCore.name: demiplane core
CP14DemiplaneCore.description: The heart of the demiplane. Your task is to take it out of the demiplane safe and sound and hand it over to the guildmaster.

CP14CashConverter.name: cash converter
CP14CashConverter.description: A simple magical device connected by small portals to the empire's central bank. It allows you to convert coins between denominations, and doesn't even charge interest! That's generous.

CP14TradingBoardBase.name: trading information board
CP14TradingBoardBase.description: Allows you to track what is selling and buying right now.

CP14TradingPortalBase.name: trade cabinet
CP14TradingPortalBase.description: A dimensional closet connected to a similar closet elsewhere. Not capable of moving living creatures, but great for trading at a distance.

CP14BaseEssenceNode.name: essence node
CP14BaseEssenceNode.description: A natural accumulation of magical essence.

CP14CrateDirtPitGrave.name: dirt pit
CP14CrateDirtPitGrave.description: There's something buried here... or someone...

CP14WallStone.name: rock
CP14WallStone.description: A solid stone natural wall. It has a cave-like coldness to it.

CP14WallStoneIndestructable.name: dense rock
CP14WallStoneIndestructable.description: An extremely durable stone. Your tools don't seem to be enough to break through it.

CP14WallDirt.name: earth wall
CP14WallDirt.description: A tall pile of dirt. Can a house be built from it?

CP14WallSnow.name: snow wall
CP14WallSnow.description: A tall pile of snow. Can a house be built from it?

CP14WallDimensit.name: dimensit wall
CP14WallDimensit.description: The solid form of the interdimensional continuum.

CP14WallStoneCopperOre.description: A solid stone natural wall. You can see the sharp flecks of copper in it.

CP14WallStoneIronOre.description: A solid stone natural wall. You can see the sharp flecks of iron in it.

CP14WallStoneGoldOre.description: A solid stone natural wall. You see the tantalizing particles of gold in it.

CP14WallStoneMithrilOre.description: A solid stone natural wall. You see the tantalizing particles of mithril in it.

CP14BaseWall.name: wall
CP14BaseWall.description: Sturdy enough to cover you from threats or cold winds.

CP14BaseWallFrame.description: This wall is now in an indeterminate state between existence and non-existence.

CP14WindowDirectional.name: directional window
CP14WindowDirectional.description: Don't smudge up the glass down there.

CP14WindowStoneBrick.name: stone brick window
CP14WindowStoneBrick.description: A stone brick wall with a glass window in it.

CP14WindowMarbleBrick.name: marble brick window
CP14WindowMarbleBrick.description: A stone brick wall with a glass window in it.

CP14AstralCorrosion.name: astral corrosion
CP14AstralCorrosion.description: Glowing cracks in reality. It's probably fine.

CP14FlameCreationArtificialFlame.name: artificial flame
CP14FlameCreationArtificialFlame.description: A magically created artificial flame burning directly into the air. Not a bad light source, or a weapon if you throw it in someone's face.

CP14LiquidDropWater.name: floating liquid drop
CP14LiquidDropWater.description: A clot of liquid held in the shape of a ball by magic

CP14ClothingCloakMaidArpon.name: maid's apron
CP14ClothingCloakMaidArpon.description: Cleanliness, orderliness and obedience are the main traits of a good maid.

CP14ClothingCloakAlchemist.name: alchemist's cloak
CP14ClothingCloakAlchemist.description: An expensive fabric that can withstand acid splashes - the standard for alchemist experts.

CP14ClothingCloakBlacksmithArpon.name: blacksmith's apron
CP14ClothingCloakBlacksmithArpon.description: Loose leather strips, still actually being clothing.

CP14ClothingCloakCaptainJacket.name: captain's jacket
CP14ClothingCloakCaptainJacket.description: the colors white and gold tell you that you're looking at a higher power.

CP14ClothingCloakCommandantJacket.name: commandant's cape
CP14ClothingCloakCommandantJacket.description: The colors white and gold tell you that you're looking at a higher power.

CP14ClothingCloakGuildmasterCape.name: guildmaster cape
CP14ClothingCloakGuildmasterCape.description: The colors green and gold tell you that you're looking at a higher power.

CP14ClothingOuterClothingGreenVest.name: green vest
CP14ClothingOuterClothingGreenVest.description: Stylish green vest with gold buttons.

CP14ClothingOuterClothingRedVest.name: red vest
CP14ClothingOuterClothingRedVest.description: Stylish red vest with gold flecks.

CP14ClothingOuterClothingBrownVest1.name: brown vest
CP14ClothingOuterClothingBrownVest1.description: A simple, decent leather vest. It's kind of stylish.

CP14ClothingOuterClothingBrownVest2.name: brown vest with clasps
CP14ClothingOuterClothingBrownVest2.description: The same plain brown leather vest, but with clasps.

CP14ClothingOuterClothingBrownVest3.name: lightweight leather vest
CP14ClothingOuterClothingBrownVest3.description: Two flaps of leather connected by a belt from below.

CP14ClothingOuterClothingJagermeisterWai.name: jagermeister's waistcoat
CP14ClothingOuterClothingJagermeisterWai.description: Doesn't interfere with movement, looks restrained. Time to go hunting.

CP14ClothingOuterClothingMerchantWaistCo.name: merchant's waistcoat
CP14ClothingOuterClothingMerchantWaistCo.description: Stylish waistcoat made of expensive leather. A special uniform for merchants that makes customers feel like beggars.

CP14MobIceSpectre.name: icy spectre
CP14MobIceSpectre.description: The unburied soul of frozen adventurers. Her rage against the world robs her of her reason.

CP14MobMonsterMosquito.name: bloodworm mosquitoes
CP14MobMonsterMosquito.description: A bloodthirsty swarm of small mosquitoes just waiting for a soft flesh for a bloody feast.

CP14MobWatcherBase.name: watcher
CP14MobWatcherBase.description: It's like it's staring right through you.

CP14FoodTomatoes.name: tomatoes
CP14FoodTomatoes.description: A red, juicy tomato. You just want to throw it in someone's face!

CP14Snowball.name: snowball
CP14Snowball.description: A small handful of snow, handy for throwing.

CP14ManaOperationGlove.name: mana glove
CP14ManaOperationGlove.description: An unsophisticated but aesthetically pleasing blend of technology and magic crystals that allows you to operate with raw mana: siphoning it from some objects and pumping it into others.

CP14CrystalLamp.name: crystal lamp
CP14CrystalLamp.description: A device that converts energy from crystals into a source of directional light.  Convenient for traveling

CP14Torch.name: torch
CP14Torch.description: At its core, a stick burning on one side. Used to light up the area.

CP14MagicHealingStaff.name: magic healing staff
CP14MagicHealingStaff.description: A long, half-tech, half-magic stick designed to convert magical energy into healing spells.

CP14BaseShield.name: shield
CP14BaseShield.description: A wooden shield capable of withstanding multiple blows.

CP14BaseMop.name: wooden mop
CP14BaseMop.description: Mop for cleaning floors from various unpleasant liquids

CP14BaseWrench.name: wrench
CP14BaseWrench.description: A common tool for assembly and disassembly. Remember: lefty latchy, righty removey.

CP14CobwebRight1.name: cobweb
CP14CobwebRight1.description: The sticky web is surprisingly strong and unpleasant.

CP14WallmountFlagBase.name: tapestry
CP14WallmountFlagBase.description: A piece of cloth pinned to the wall.

CP14WallmauntGarlandBase.name: crystals garland
CP14WallmauntGarlandBase.description: Carefully crafted sparkling crystals tied on a string. For a festive attitude.

CP14IronDoor.name: iron door
CP14IronDoor.description: Well, if there's a solid iron door, there must be something valuable behind it.

CP14IronDoorWindowed.name: iron windowed door
CP14IronDoorWindowed.description: a solid iron door with a small window. You can look through it, of course, but it's hard to put your hand through.

CP14WoodenDoor.name: wooden door
CP14WoodenDoor.description: Not the most solid construction, but it's better than nothing.

CP14WoodenDoorWindowed.name: wooden windowed door
CP14WoodenDoorWindowed.description: Not the most solid construction, but it's better than nothing.

CP14GatherableWaterAirLily.name: air lily
CP14GatherableWaterAirLily.description: A light, delicate and airy flower. It is said that its special properties even allow it to breathe underwater...

CP14BaseBarrel.name: wooden barrel
CP14BaseBarrel.description: The simplest design for storing liquids.

CP14CraneBarrel.name: wooden crane barrel
CP14CraneBarrel.description: Large lying barrel with tap, for storing valuable liquids.

CP14CraneBarrelSmall.name: wooden small crane barrel
CP14CraneBarrelSmall.description: A small lying barrel with a tap to quickly pour liquid into mugs.

CP14BenchWood.name: wood bench
CP14BenchWood.description: A bench carved from wood, a comfortable part of the interior designed for sitting and relaxing.

CP14ChairWooden.name: wooden chair
CP14ChairWooden.description: Made of the most common planks. Simple and effective!

CP14Mannequin.name: mannequin
CP14Mannequin.description: A handy stand for clothing or armour.

CP14Safe.name: safe
CP14Safe.description: A giant iron box for storing your most precious possessions. Extremely heavy and extremely strong.

CP14TargetStake.name: target stake
CP14TargetStake.description: A wooden stand on which to fix a target for firing.

CP14TargetEffigy.name: target effigy
CP14TargetEffigy.description: The target is a scarecrow for practising close combat strikes.... or magic.

CP14WallmountLampEmpty.name: crystal wall lamp
CP14WallmountLampEmpty.description: A simple wallmount magical device that converts crystal energy into bright light.

CP14WallmountOrdersBorder.name: orders board
CP14WallmountOrdersBorder.description: Is there a job for a witcher?

CP14Workbench.name: workbench
CP14Workbench.description: Table for the production of various basic tools.

CP14WorkbenchCooking.name: cooking table
CP14WorkbenchCooking.description: A table to work with food. Time to cook!

CP14WorkbenchSewing.name: sewing table
CP14WorkbenchSewing.description: A table with embroidery tools to create different clothing and materials.

CP14AlchemySolutionCleaner.name: solution cleaner
CP14AlchemySolutionCleaner.description: An alchemical device that destroys from a solution poured into it the reagent that is least in the solution. Requires an energy crystal to operate.

CP14BaseVat.name: big vat
CP14BaseVat.description: A very large vat for storing huge amounts of liquid. Heavy, uncomfortable to carry.

CP14WorkbenchAnvil.name: anvil
CP14WorkbenchAnvil.description: A big piece of metal that allows you to turn square pieces of metal into pieces of metal in other, more useful shapes.

CP14WorkbenchFurnace.name: melting furnace
CP14WorkbenchFurnace.description: A red-hot stone construction that allows ores to be smelted into pure metal

CP14EssenceCollector.name: essence collector
CP14EssenceCollector.description: Being powered by the energy crystal, it will start sucking in all the essence floating in the air and converting it into useful liquid.

CP14EssenceSplitter.name: essence splitter
CP14EssenceSplitter.description: A device capable of splitting objects into magical essence when overloaded with energy.

CP14WoodenChest.name: wooden chest
CP14WoodenChest.description: A simple wooden chest for easy storage of junk.

CP14CrateCoffin.name: coffin
CP14CrateCoffin.description: A comfortable and nice looking coffin to comfortably await your resurrection.

CP14WallLeaf.name: leaf wall
